A Los Angeles stuntwoman is considering suing a Nickelodeon show after she seriously injured herself with a stunt gone terribly wrong.

Katina Waters, 40, was hired to be slowly dropped from the ceiling for an episode of 'iCarly' on which she appeared in 2011.

She instead was allowed to smash into the ground, fracturing her legs and tearing ligaments.

Suing: Katina Waters is a Hollywood stuntwoman who was dropped during a stunt for the Nickelodeon show iCarly

TMZ reports the 'person operating "the descender machine"' could be at fault for dropping her without warning, giving her grounds to sue.

Schneider's Bakery Productions, Nickelodeon and MTV Networks may be targeted with the legal action claiming cash for pain and suffering caused in the accident as well as for the earnings she may have lost due to her injuries.

iCarly was a wildly popular show aimed at tweens and teens that taped in Hollywood and starred Miranda Cosgrove as Carly, a teen who made a web comedy with her group of friends.

It aired from 2009 until 2012.

